`src/conformance/governed-surface-allowlist.json`; AC-079 UNMINTED).

Two net-new governed methods on `Engine` declare and inspect projections over
interpretive attributes. The facade re-exports the five supporting
`Projection*` types (all part of the public Rust surface):

- `Engine::configure_projections(specs: &[ProjectionSpec], drop: &[String]) ->
  Result<ProjectionDelta, EngineError>` — declarative, idempotent apply: the
  engine is the SOLE projection authority (C-1) and diffs `specs` against the
  durable registry, backfilling the difference in one write transaction. `drop`
  is EXPLICIT — omitting a live projection from `specs` does NOT drop it; removal
  requires naming it in `drop`. A destructive change (a role removal or a
  tokenizer/embedder change) without a drop is refused with
  `EngineError::ProjectionDestructive { name, delta }` — the delta names what the
  caller must drop. Re-applying an unchanged spec returns
  `ProjectionDelta { unchanged: true, .. }` with the vecs empty.
- `Engine::read_projections() -> Result<Vec<ProjectionSpec>, EngineError>` — the
  registry introspection (the Rust analogue of `read.projections`), sorted by
  name. Pure read; never mutates.

Types:

- `ProjectionSpec { name: String, roles: BTreeSet<ProjectionRole>, fts:
  Option<ProjectionFts>, vector: Option<ProjectionVector> }`. `roles` carries SET
  semantics (an attribute can be `Filterable` AND `Searchable`).
- `ProjectionRole` — exactly three variants: `Filterable`, `Rankable`,
  `Searchable` (`searchable→FTS` and `searchable→vector` are tier labels carried
  by the `fts`/`vector` sub-objects, not roles). `as_str` / `from_str_opt` give
  the `"filterable" | "rankable" | "searchable"` wire spellings.
- `ProjectionFts { tokenizer: Option<String> }` and `ProjectionVector { embedder:
  Option<String> }` — the `searchable→FTS` / `searchable→vector` sub-target
  selectors (`None` ⇒ engine default). Slice 20 attaches `dense_readiness` to
  `ProjectionVector` additively.
- `ProjectionDelta { built, dropped, deferred, unchanged }`. Cheap roles
  (`filterable`, `searchable→FTS`) build same-transaction; `rankable` and the
  `searchable→vector` sub-target are persisted-but-deferred (reported in
  `deferred`, never an error).

**Projection-name contract (0.8.20 Slice 15d fix-4).** A projection `name` is an
app-declared identifier that becomes a SQLite JSON-path key (`$."<name>"`) at
write time, so `configure_projections` REJECTS — with
`EngineError::InvalidArgument` naming the offending value — any spec or `drop`
name that cannot round-trip through that quoted-key form: an empty name, a name
containing a double-quote `"`, a name containing a BACKSLASH `\`, or a name
containing any ASCII control char. This upholds the invariant "a name the engine
ACCEPTS is populatable" (accept ⟹ works); previously a backslash name was
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15-steward-positions-verify-20260721T041028Z.log:2628:dev/steward/steward-ledger.jsonl:90:{"ts": "2026-07-20T21:51:14.863Z", "seq": 90, "kind": "decision", "summary": "Slice 15 PARTIAL landed — TC-34 + search-validity coherence; KEYSTONE NOT BUILT, 20/25 BLOCKED; TC-40/41 need HITL ratification before the registry", "decider": "steward", "detail": "Slice 15 returned PARTIALLY COMPLETE and said so plainly. Steward verified from primary sources: branch 7ef4e799, 11 commits, clean, local-only; SCHEMA 22; cargo check AND clippy --workspace --all-targets re-run by the steward on BOTH branch and combined main = 0/0; recovery_denylist parsed from JSON = exactly five; AC-079 UNMINTED and the allowlist entry reads AWAITING HITL SIGN-OFF (3 occurrences); codex 9 four rounds to TERMINAL PASS, no overrides. FALSE-SIGN-OFF AUDIT: 'HITL-SIGNED' appears 18x in the diff, which superficially contradicted the orchestrator's 'only one' claim — steward inspected every occurrence: all are closure-artifact JSON ASSERTING nothing was signed, plus one code comment citing a historical Decision-5 from 2026-06-05. NO false sign-off. LANDED: (a) TC-34 node-validity authoring as OPTIONAL FIELDS on the existing node write item (INTEGER epoch), symmetric with PreparedWrite::Edge's t_valid/t_invalid — NOT a new verb, zero new commands, allowlist membership byte-unchanged, validation centralised in engine validate_write; (b) SEARCH-VALIDITY COHERENCE, unscoped and found by codex: 'search' ignored validity windows ENTIRELY because Slice 10 scoped ReadView to five read verbs and omitted search — latent while nobody could author a window, made LIVE by TC-34. Fixed at FIVE hydration sites (codex cited one); validity had also been applied AFTER the vector KNN cutoff (RED reproduced ZERO hits for a query with two valid matches) and the graph arm re-read the clock independently. STATED LIMITATION, not papered over: vector recall restored only within the existing 192-candidate pool. NOT DONE — R-20-PR registry, R-20-EAV, and TC-33 implementation are DESIGN-ONLY. SLICES 20 AND 25 REMAIN BLOCKED. STEWARD ENDORSES the orchestrator's judgement call to fix the read path rather than build the keystone on top of a search that ignores validity — building the projection registry over an incoherent read path would have baked the incoherence into the Phase-2 keystone that 20/25/30 all depend on. ESCALATED TO HITL (record/direction changes, NOT steward-decidable): TC-40/TC-41 — the plan's ProjectionSpec 'roles: {filterable, rankable, searchable}' as THREE BOOLEANS cannot express the ratified C-1 contract (C-1 Q4 tiering needs searchable->FTS and searchable->vector separately declarable; the staleness contract splits them same-transaction vs async; and Slice 20's dense_readiness attaches ONLY to searchable->vector, so a boolean gives Slice 20 nothing to attach to). Memex already landed AttributeSpec.index: Set[ProjectionRole] inert at 95ed450, so the engine must accept a SET or the ratified seam does not connect — and Slice 30's H7 gate mechanically checks as-built code against the contract, so the boolean shape would FAIL Slice 30 and HOLD THE BREAKING PAIR. Also owed: scoping 'filterable' to the read/EAV backend (vec0 pre-KNN filtering cannot be extended without recreating the table and re-embedding the corpus; the post-KNN fallback is type-rejected by ADR-0.8.11 D3) is a DEVIATION from the contract's 'pre-KNN' wording and needs ratification, not assumption. TC-33: the orchestrator's design work CONFIRMS the steward's INTEGER recommendation (no escalation on the merits); it flags one layering call — storage and the governed SDK surface become INTEGER while the BYO-LLM extractor JSON keeps ISO-8601 with engine-side normalisation, because an LLM cannot reliably emit epoch seconds. STEWARD ENDORSES that as a genuine layering boundary rather than splitting the difference, subject to HITL veto. TC-33 also needs step 24 (23 being EAV) = FOUR migrations in 0.8.20 against I-6's one-per-release; I-6 is unenforced guidance and already exceeded — surfaced, not slipped. TC-42 (process, CONFIRMED BY STEWARD): a RED test named in the Slice-0 acceptance table, valid_as_of_binds_now_once (dev/design/0.8.20-slice0-erasure-design.md:308), has ZERO hits in src/ — it was never written, R-20-NV was closed at Slice 10 anyway, and the property it guarded then REGRESSED in fix-2. Traceability from Slice-0 acceptance tables to real tests is unenforced; Slice 40 must check it mechanically. Found by accident, so assume it is not the only one. ORCHESTRATOR SELF-REPORTED ERROR (good practice): it passed an unverified 'no index on canonical_nodes(write_cursor)' claim into a closure brief; a partial index does exist (canonical_nodes_state_active_idx, step 20); its subagent refused to transcribe it.", "refs": ["git:e32497a2", "branch:orch-0.8.20-s15", "slice:15"]}
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15-steward-positions-verify-20260721T041028Z.log:2727:dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl:2:{"ts": "2026-07-08T00:44:21.780Z", "seq": 2, "kind": "proposal", "summary": "SHOT 1 (FATHOM opens) — C-1 EntityTypeSpec->ProjectionSpec co-design. Full text: OPP-12-C1-shot1.md. ProjectionSpec {name, roles:Set<{filterable,rankable,searchable}>, fts?:{tokenizer}, vector?:{embedder}} via configure_projections(spec,drop?), idempotent diff+backfill, projecting from a net-new engine EAV+property-FTS, wrapping the shipped EXP-S per-kind seam (TC-1); async worker already exists (engine:876-887). Proposed mapping: AttributeSpec.key->ProjectionSpec.name; py_type scalar->filterable; str free-text->searchable+fts; graded dial->rankable (F9-gated ~0.8.16); relationships->typed-edge filterable. VERIFIED GAP: Memex AttributeSpec carries NO role field (EAV=group/key/value) -> role source must be co-designed.", "cx": "C-1", "opp": "OPP-12", "shot": "1", "status": "posted-pending-hitl-review", "voice": "FATHOM", "refs": ["file:dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-C1-shot1.md", "opp:OPP-12"], "body": "CONVERGENCE QUESTIONS FOR MEMEX (bounded, answer in SHOT 2):\nQ1 (highest leverage) Role source: does AttributeSpec carry an explicit optional role hint (index: Set[ProjectionRole]) with engine py_type-inference as default when absent? ProjectionSpec needs a role source and has none. RECOMMEND: add the optional field NOW in Commission C -- adding it post-lock re-serializes every persisted WMEntityTypeSpec.\nQ2 EAV convergence: converge on ONE engine-owned EAV (Memex stops writing app-side WorldModelEntityAttribute) or does the projection read FROM Memex's governed-node EAV? 'Converges' is named with no mechanism (under-specified both sides).\nQ3 Idempotent re-registration + drift authority: confirm ENGINE is the sole projection authority via configure_projections diff (Memex never runs a 2nd projection registry); incompatible change (embedder/tokenizer swap on an existing name) surfaces a destructive delta requiring explicit drop -- accepted?\nQ4 provisional/promotion: do provisional=True types get projections immediately (adaptive-loop recall) or only on promote()? If immediate, does a rejected provisional trigger a projection drop (rebuild churn)?\nQ5 R-A persist boundary: PROPOSAL -- Memex persists the spec (WMEntityTypeSpec); the engine ProjectionSpec is a DERIVED cache re-driven idempotently on boot; engine never persists a spec Memex can't re-derive -> one durable source of truth, no 2nd persistent registry to sync. Confirm.\nQ6 rankable/F9 + surrogate id: (a) F9 lands ~0.8.16; can C-1 co-land (0.9.1) ship filterable+searchable only, rankable grafting when F9 lands? (b) how does EntityTypeSpec.id_prefix reconcile with the engine-minted surrogate logical_id for entities that begin anonymous?\n\nCO-LAND / TIMING ASK: Freeze NOW in Commission C (does NOT foreclose C-1): EntityTypeSpec/AttributeSpec shape, JSON serialization, R-A persistence, register() single entry point. ONE forward-compat ask: land the optional per-AttributeSpec role hint (Q1) in Commission C now -- the only field whose later addition is a breaking re-serialization. Must WAIT for FathomDB 0.9.1: configure_projections/ProjectionSpec, engine EAV+property-FTS, dense_readiness. DECISION FORCED THIS LOOP: agree Q1 (role hint) + Q5 (engine-as-derived-cache) before Commission C locks AttributeSpec; Q2/Q3 may co-design to the 0.9.1 P2-S0 ADR but flag open now so neither side over-builds an EAV the other discards."}
