e (embedder/tokenizer swap on an existing name) surfaces a destructive delta requiring explicit drop -- accepted?\nQ4 provisional/promotion: do provisional=True types get projections immediately (adaptive-loop recall) or only on promote()? If immediate, does a rejected provisional trigger a projection drop (rebuild churn)?\nQ5 R-A persist boundary: PROPOSAL -- Memex persists the spec (WMEntityTypeSpec); the engine ProjectionSpec is a DERIVED cache re-driven idempotently on boot; engine never persists a spec Memex can't re-derive -> one durable source of truth, no 2nd persistent registry to sync. Confirm.\nQ6 rankable/F9 + surrogate id: (a) F9 lands ~0.8.16; can C-1 co-land (0.9.1) ship filterable+searchable only, rankable grafting when F9 lands? (b) how does EntityTypeSpec.id_prefix reconcile with the engine-minted surrogate logical_id for entities that begin anonymous?\n\nCO-LAND / TIMING ASK: Freeze NOW in Commission C (does NOT foreclose C-1): EntityTypeSpec/AttributeSpec shape, JSON serialization, R-A persistence, register() single entry point. ONE forward-compat ask: land the optional per-AttributeSpec role hint (Q1) in Commission C now -- the only field whose later addition is a breaking re-serialization. Must WAIT for FathomDB 0.9.1: configure_projections/ProjectionSpec, engine EAV+property-FTS, dense_readiness. DECISION FORCED THIS LOOP: agree Q1 (role hint) + Q5 (engine-as-derived-cache) before Commission C locks AttributeSpec; Q2/Q3 may co-design to the 0.9.1 P2-S0 ADR but flag open now so neither side over-builds an EAV the other discards."}
