 LIMITATION, not papered over: vector recall restored only within the existing 192-candidate pool. NOT DONE — R-20-PR registry, R-20-EAV, and TC-33 implementation are DESIGN-ONLY. SLICES 20 AND 25 REMAIN BLOCKED. STEWARD ENDORSES the orchestrator's judgement call to fix the read path rather than build the keystone on top of a search that ignores validity — building the projection registry over an incoherent read path would have baked the incoherence into the Phase-2 keystone that 20/25/30 all depend on. ESCALATED TO HITL (record/direction changes, NOT steward-decidable): TC-40/TC-41 — the plan's ProjectionSpec 'roles: {filterable, rankable, searchable}' as THREE BOOLEANS cannot express the ratified C-1 contract (C-1 Q4 tiering needs searchable->FTS and searchable->vector separately declarable; the staleness contract splits them same-transaction vs async; and Slice 20's dense_readiness attaches ONLY to searchable->vector, so a boolean gives Slice 20 nothing to attach to). Memex already landed AttributeSpec.index: Set[ProjectionRole] inert at 95ed450, so the engine must accept a SET or the ratified seam does not connect — and Slice 30's H7 gate mechanically checks as-built code against the contract, so the boolean shape would FAIL Slice 30 and HOLD THE BREAKING PAIR. Also owed: scoping 'filterable' to the read/EAV backend (vec0 pre-KNN filtering cannot be extended without recreating the table and re-embedding the corpus; the post-KNN fallback is type-rejected by ADR-0.8.11 D3) is a DEVIATION from the contract's 'pre-KNN' wording and needs ratification, not assumption. TC-33: the orchestrator's design work CONFIRMS the steward's INTEGER recommendation (no escalation on the merits); it flags one layering call — storage and the governed SDK surface become INTEGER while the BYO-LLM extractor JSON keeps ISO-8601 with engine-side normalisation, because an LLM cannot reliably emit epoch seconds. STEWARD ENDORSES that as a genuine layering boundary rather than splitting the difference, subject to HITL veto. TC-33 also needs step 24 (23 being EAV) = FOUR migrations in 0.8.20 against I-6's one-per-release; I-6 is unenforced guidance and already exceeded — surfaced, not slipped. TC-42 (process, CONFIRMED BY STEWARD): a RED test named in the Slice-0 acceptance table, valid_as_of_binds_now_once (dev/design/0.8.20-slice0-erasure-design.md:308), has ZERO hits in src/ — it was never written, R-20-NV was closed at Slice 10 anyway, and the property it guarded then REGRESSED in fix-2. Traceability from Slice-0 acceptance tables to real tests is unenforced; Slice 40 must check it mechanically. Found by accident, so assume it is not the only one. ORCHESTRATOR SELF-REPORTED ERROR (good practice): it passed an unverified 'no index on canonical_nodes(write_cursor)' claim into a closure brief; a partial index does exist (canonical_nodes_state_active_idx, step 20); its subagent refused to transcribe it.", "refs": ["git:e32497a2", "branch:orch-0.8.20-s15", "slice:15"]}
