codex
The new projection API can return misleading deltas and perform unnecessary backfills when duplicate projection names are supplied in one request. This is an actionable correctness issue in the newly introduced diffing logic.

Review comment:

- [P2] Reject duplicate projection names before diffing — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15d/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:15159-15162
  When a caller supplies the same projection `name` more than once in a single `configure_projections` call, every spec is compared against this one pre-loop `current` snapshot rather than the rows already persisted earlier in the loop. On a fresh DB, `[searchable+fts, rankable-only]` for the same name will backfill the first spec, then overwrite the registry with the second while returning a delta that still reports the first build/defer outcome; duplicate `drop` entries have the same stale-snapshot problem and can be reported more than once. Rejecting or coalescing duplicate names up front keeps the registry and `ProjectionDelta` aligned with the accepted input.
